               <p>WILLIAM ALDRIDGE. I am a <rs id="t18320906-265-viclabel1488" type="occupation">coachman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-265-victim2168 t18320906-265-viclabel1488"></join>, and live in Mount-street. On the 28th of August, about half-past eight o'clock in the evening, I was in <placeName id="t18320906-265-crimeloc1489">Long-lane, Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-265-crimeloc1489" type="placeName" value="Long-lane, Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-265-crimeloc1489" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-265-off1486 t18320906-265-crimeloc1489"></join>; I did not feel my handkerchief taken till I received information - it was produced to me about two minutes afterwards, when the prisoner was secured.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-265-person2169">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COLTON
               <interp inst="t18320906-265-person2169" type="surname" value="COLTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-265-person2169" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-265-person2169" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a broker, and was in Longalley. I observed the prisoner and another following Mr. Aldridge, who had a female with him, and near the end of Long-lane I saw the other take the handkerchief out of Aldridge's pocket, and pass it behind to the prisoner, who went into a shop - I stopped Aldridge, and told him; Cadby went in, and took the prisoner; the other ran away - I took Aldridge to the shop where the prisoner was.</p>
               <p>JOSEPH CADBY. I am a constable. I was in Longlane, with Colton; the prisoner, and another followed the prosecutor; they made several attempts; at last the other got the handkerchief out, and gave it to the prisoner, who went into a shop - I went, and took him; I found the handkerchief under his coat; I do not think I should know the other.(Property produced and sworn</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I hope the prosecutor will recommend me to mercy.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18320906-265-verdict1490" type="verdictDescription">
